Description: BestCalls.com operates an Internet directory of investor events.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: BestCalls.com was the industry's first earnings conference call directory for individual investors.  Founder Mark Coker started BestCalls after he was denied access to an earnings conference call by Legato Systems (story at http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Individual-Shareholders-Have-the-Power-With-New-2938601.php).  The company lobbied the SEC for open access to conference calls, and was ultimately one of several catalysts for the SEC's REGULATION FAIR DISCLOSURE, a.k.a. "Reg FD."  Reg FD provided publicly traded companies permission to satisfy their fair disclosure obligations by allowing all investors on their earnings conference calls.  BestCalls was acquired by Shareholder.com in April 2003.  Shareholder.com was acquired by the NASDAQ stock exchange the next year.  NASDAQ continued operating BestCalls for another five or six years before ending the service.
Industry Groups: Events, Financial Services, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment

Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Eco-Source Technologies (EST) is an energy service company (ESCO) delivering turnkey energy efficiency and renewable energy solutions to the global marketplace. We promote energy efficiency by offering innovative products, resource-efficient planning and services guaranteed to counteract skyrocketing energy costs. Initially, we target the required energy demands of a consumer’s infrastructure in order to identify solutions that meet the precise energy needs of the enterprise and its stakeholders. Central to our business is the delivery of performance and savings guarantees through our energy performance contracts (EPCs). This is an arrangement where we design, implement and finance all necessary investments in an energy efficiency or renewable energy project. Our guarantee is that the cost of a project will be recovered from the energy savings as well as assuming certain performance risks during the project’s economic lifetime by some of our remuneration being directly tied to the energy savings achieved. By entering into an EPC with Eco-Source Technologies, customers can receive complete project financing, installation, and guaranteed results simultaneously. Where traditional contracting activities focus on managing the scope of the project, our activity focuses on managing the outcome of the project.
Founders: Darryl Sanders, Geoffrey Pottinger, Kevin James

Description: ZT Technology Solutions provides government, telecommunications, and enterprise customers with technology solutions.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ZT Technology Solutions was founded in 2010 to provide government, telecommunications, and enterprise customers with technology solutions to address their product and service life cycle needs, especially for legacy products. ZT‘s fundament belief is that legacy products will remain in the telecom network indefinitely. ZT’s founders, Mike Dazio and John Tsimaras, started this company with one specific mission: Maintain, enhance and support many of the legacy products that are currently in the Public Switched Telephone Network. Mr. Dazio and Mr. Tsimaras bring their vast experience and expertise to this company. Mr. Dazio served as a Product Manager at AT&T/Western Electric/Lucent Technologies for over 25 years. Per Mr. Dazio, the goal of a product manager is to extend the life of legacy products and assist customers to migrate eventually to newer technologies. Mr. Tsimaras headed hardware development groups at AT&T/Western Electric/Lucent Technologies and Datatek Applications for nearly 30 years. One product on which they both worked was a legacy data networking product called Datakit VCS. It was initially deployed in the mid 1980’s. To this day the telephone companies, both foreign and domestic, still have over one billion dollars of this product in use in their networks. Despite the rise of newer technologies, like IP, LTE, there still is a need to support async, X.25 etc. in the circuit-switched world. Mr. Dazio understood this and helped create a company called Datatek Applications in 1998 simply to continue to enhance and support the Datakit VCS product line. Today that company is still providing support.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Hardware, Information Technology, Software

Description: Industrial Business Solutions is an Engineering and Technology company providing field service and software.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Industrial Business Solutions is an international services and software company providing solutions to control operational risk in high risk industrial environments. IBS was established as an owners Consulting Services and Business Systems Company servicing industrial production and manufacturing facilities in the Oil & Gas, Refining, and Power and Mining market. IBS is structured into two business divisions. The plant and capital project services division and Systems division. Continuum Edge®, comprised of a collection of advanced web applications, manages the entire safety spectrum of industrial operations and critical safety communications. Click below to see how IBS can improve your execution of daily operations.  ContinuumEdge is a web based management system designed to dramatically improve work processes, asset information, change management, and overall effectiveness of job planning, preparation and execution. With a modular structure, ContinuumEdge is comprised of three different types of modules that work in unison to provide a system management solution tailor made to your needs. Application Modules include: - Completions & Commissioning Management System (CCMS), - Safety Risk Management System (SRMS), - Operability Development Management System (ODMS) Sub-Modules are the building blocks used to tailor the ContinuumEdge system specifically to your organization's requirements. Currently over 30 sub modules are available, with more being developed all the time. So if you have a specific function that needs to be managed, we can develop a module for it. Sub-Modules include; Motor Management & Efficiency Calculator, Instrument Calibration, Loop Testing, and many more. ContinuumEdge is designed to: - Centralize information required for risk analysis and safety document development, - Standardize the development and "linking" of Critical Safety Documentation, - Manage detailed plant information and eliminate inaccurate or conflicting data, - Improve Document Searching through information integration and advanced queries, and - Communicate with other applications to improve change management All applications are available in English, Spanish, and Portuguese.

Changing their communities for the better requires changing a culture that takes Black people for granted and changing policies and laws that make us criminals and keep resources from their communities. To get there, They work to understand the dynamics impacting their communities; they build the capacity of their communities to govern; and they engage and include Black people in the decisions that impact their lives. There are three ways that Black Futures Lab is a different kind of project for change: their mission to engage Black voters year-round; their commitment to use their political strength to stop corporate influences from creeping into progressive policies; and their plan to combine technology and traditional organizing methods to reach Black people anywhere and everywhere they are.

Full Description: WTVY stresses the importance of health and safety to the company and its employees. Upon the arrival of the Coronavirus pandemic in March 2020, Gray Television immediately instituted a broad range of policies and protocols to protect its employees, and they continually refined them as issues arose. The company directed employees to work from home as much as possible in early March 2020 and invested heavily in new technologies to make that option widely available. Employees were soon assured that we would not impose any layoffs, furloughs, benefit cuts, or delay of benefits during the pandemic. Paid time off was provided for mandatory quarantines, and health insurance copays were covered. To support their safety, they provided masks, sanitizers, cleaning supplies, and other items to employees and each work location. In general, they followed CDC guidelines in their policies and procedures, which often meant that they had to modify their operations as guidelines changed.
